review:
  thoroughness: medium
  understanding: medium
  rating: neutral
issues:
- id: missing-safety-comments-at-teddy-call-sites
  severity: low
  comment: |
    Several `unsafe { ... }` blocks in packed/teddy/builder.rs lack
    the literal `// SAFETY:` prefix at the call site, even though
    the feature-detection guard immediately above is the safety
    invariant. Specifically: lines 482 (SlimSSSE3::new_unchecked),
    546 (SlimAVX2::new_unchecked), 618 (FatAVX2::new_unchecked),
    and 748 (SlimNeon::new_unchecked — no guard at all because Neon
    is unconditionally available on aarch64 targets where the cfg
    applies). The dozens of `unsafe { test() }` blocks in
    packed/vector.rs follow the same pattern. Per rubric §2 this
    caps rating at neutral; the underlying invariants ARE upheld.
- id: no-miri-in-ci
  severity: low
  comment: |
    .github/workflows/ci.yml runs cargo test across a matrix of
    OS/arch/Rust versions but does not invoke `cargo miri test`.
    The pointer-arithmetic helpers (packed/ext.rs::distance,
    packed/pattern.rs::is_equal_raw call sites) are miri-testable;
    the SIMD intrinsics are not. Caps independently at positive;
    the §2 neutral cap dominates.
comment: |-
  Reviewed crate published at version 1.1.3 by Andrew Gallant
  (BurntSushi). Used pervasively as the multi-pattern search engine
  underneath `regex`, so this code is exercised by essentially the
  entire Rust ecosystem. Read all 32 .rs files under src/, Cargo.toml,
  README.md, DESIGN.md, .github/workflows/ci.yml.
  
  Concern #1 (malicious/suspicious): Cargo.toml declares no build
  script (no `build` field, no build.rs in tarball). No proc-macro
  (this is a regular library). No `include_bytes!`, no
  `std::process::Command`, no network APIs, no obfuscation. The
  large data table in src/util/byte_frequencies.rs is a documented
  256-entry byte frequency distribution used for prefilter heuristics
  (transparent purpose). Dependencies: optional `memchr` (also by
  BurntSushi) and optional `log`. License Unlicense OR MIT,
  repository link valid, author plausible.
  
  Concern #2 (unsafe + SAFETY): 227 unsafe occurrences across 10
  files. Concentrated in src/packed/vector.rs (161) and
  src/packed/teddy/{generic,builder}.rs (52 combined) — the SIMD
  Teddy implementation. Pattern is overwhelmingly `unsafe fn`
  declarations with rustdoc `# Safety` sections (idiomatic for
  vendor-intrinsic wrappers gated on `#[target_feature]`). Core
  algorithm files (dfa.rs, nfa/{contiguous,noncontiguous}.rs,
  ahocorasick.rs, automaton.rs) have only `unsafe trait Automaton`
  + `unsafe impl ... for ...`, justified by a multi-line comment
  block describing the soundness contract.
  
  Call sites WITH `// SAFETY:` comments: packed/pattern.rs:300/332,
  packed/teddy/builder.rs:362, packed/teddy/builder.rs:512.
  
  Call sites WITHOUT the literal `// SAFETY:` prefix:
  packed/teddy/builder.rs:482, 546, 618, 748 (the Slim/Fat
  *::new_unchecked wrappers — invariant is the feature-detection
  guard immediately above, except SlimNeon which has none because
  Neon is unconditional on aarch64-with-the-relevant-cfg), plus
  ~40 `unsafe { test() }` blocks in packed/vector.rs test code.
  Per rubric §2 this caps the rating at neutral.
  
  Concern #3 (miri): .github/workflows/ci.yml has no miri job. The
  pure-Rust unsafe (pointer distance, is_equal_raw) is in principle
  miri-testable; the SIMD intrinsics are not (miri does not execute
  vendor intrinsics gated on target_feature). Caps at positive;
  dominated by the §2 cap.
  
  Concern #4 (correctness): No obvious bugs. SmallIndex
  (util/primitives.rs) carefully constrains automaton state IDs to
  fit u32/usize/isize on all targets, returning errors on overflow
  rather than panicking. The Aho-Corasick construction in
  nfa/noncontiguous.rs and the DFA in dfa.rs follow the textbook
  algorithm with leftmost-first/longest variants documented in
  DESIGN.md. Public API does extensive input validation (e.g.
  AhoCorasickBuilder returns BuildError for too-many-patterns).
  Spot-checked is_prefix_raw (packed/pattern.rs:265) — length
  pre-check before the unsafe call is correct. Did NOT walk every
  state-transition implementation; thoroughness is medium.
  
  Did NOT run any code (no cargo build/test/expand) per project
  rules.
----- SIGN CREV PROOF -----
