comment: |-
  Reviewed as a delta against 1.1.3. The on-disk diff is ~46 lines
  total, entirely clippy/style cleanups: redundant borrows removed
  (`&haystack` -> `haystack`, `&self.0` -> `self.0`), `.map(|p|
  p.clone())` -> `.cloned()` at src/dfa.rs:497, `'b` lifetime
  collapsed to `'_` at src/nfa/contiguous.rs:824, redundant `b as
  u8` cast removed at src/util/prefilter.rs:552, the unstable
  feature flag in src/lib.rs:230 switched from `doc_auto_cfg` to
  `doc_cfg`, plus Cargo manifest normalization by a newer Cargo
  toolchain (adds `build = false`, `autolib = false`, `autobins =
  false`, etc.).
  
  Concern #1: no changes — no build.rs added, no new deps, no
  proc-macro flip, no obfuscation. Author and license unchanged.
  
  Concern #2: zero changes to `unsafe` blocks or `// SAFETY:`
  comments. Same SAFETY-comment-missing situation in
  packed/teddy/builder.rs at lines 482, 546, 618, 748 as in 1.1.3.
  
  Concern #3: .github/workflows/ci.yml unchanged in any
  miri-relevant way. Still no miri job.
  
  Concern #4: nothing in the diff alters semantics — the removed
  borrows/casts compile to identical code, and the lifetime change
  is purely cosmetic. No new bug shapes introduced.
  
  Did NOT run any code. Rating inherited from 1.1.3: neutral.
